          <msContents class="lemmatic">
            <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms
                            attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="n 80119944 ">Hippocrates</persName>. </summary>
            <msItem>
              <author>
                <name type="person" key="n 80145641" ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624" subtype="aut">
                  <persName xml:lang="eng">Ḥunayn ibn Isḥāq‏</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="ara">حنين بن إسحق</persName>
                </name>
              </author>
              <title>
                <title xml:lang="ara">شرح فصول أبقراط لجالينوس</title>
                <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc">Galen's Commentary on the
                                    Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                <title xml:lang="eng" type="alt">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ
                                    li-Gālīnūs</title>
              </title>
              <note> This is a collection of the Hippocratic lemmata of <persName key="n 80145641" ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624">Ḥunayn</persName>'s version. The
                                beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk 1: 1b (The first folios
                                [ff. 1b-4b] are written by another hand); Bk 2: 7a; Bk 3: [missing
                                start]; Bk 4: 11a; Bk 5: 17a; Bk 6: 22b; Bk 7: 25b. </note>
